Definitions 
DNS - (Domain Name System) traffic is the flow of queries and responses between your device and a DNS server
TCP - (Transmission Control Protocol) traffic is the flow of data packets over a network using a connection-oriented standard
HTTP - (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) is the fundamental set of rules that allows web browsers and servers to communicate
